’Ů@e20a63c2bf98bb9ff21c090eb615f171b8bb48b2085d11b0871f83b4b735116dÚŢTitle: title: plugin add
Path: Examples
Content:
Run the 
``nu_plugin_inc``
 plugin from the current directory or $env.NU_PLUGIN_DIRS and install its signatures.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> plugin add nu_plugin_inc


```
Run the 
``nu_plugin_polars``
 plugin from the current directory or $env.NU_PLUGIN_DIRS, and install its signatures to the "polars.msgpackz" plugin registry file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> plugin add --plugin-config polars.msgpackz nu_plugin_polars


```
’Ů@1916e9c3b07a2b97f460a4f07d25cb928771fc771fbe7d7aebb7ad558aeb20f1ÚuTitle: title: plugin add
Path: Notes
Content:
This does not load the plugin commands into the scope - see 
``plugin use``
 for

that.
Instead, it runs the plugin to get its command signatures, and then edits the

plugin registry file (by default, 
``$nu.plugin-path``
). The changes will be

apparent the next time 
``nu``
 is next launched with that plugin registry file.
